==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sulphonic
<hw>Sul*phon"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Pertaining to, or derived from, a sulphone; -- used specifically to
designate any one of a series of acids (regarded as acid ethereal salts
of sulphurous acid) obtained by the oxidation of the mercaptans, or by
treating sulphuric acid with certain aromatic bases (as benzene);
<as>as, phenyl <ex>sulphonic</ex> acid, <chform>C6H5.SO2.OH</chform>, a
stable colorless crystalline substance</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Sulphonic group</b></col> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>, <cd>the
hypothetical radical, <chform>SO2.OH</chform>, the characteristic
residue of sulphonic acids.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sulphonium</ent>⟦br⟧
